SCULPTURE. Head entirely reticulate-punctate, including antennal scrobe. Mesosoma entirely reticulatepunctate, except for katepisternum which is smooth (
Fig. 6B
). Fourth abdominal tergite reticulatepunctate almost entirely. Length of basigastral costulae, in dorsal view, less than half the length of postpetiole.

SETAE. Cephalic ground-setae remiform (Fig, 6A). Two pairs of remiform erect setae on cephalic dorsum; both pairs located in the posterior third of cephalic dorsum, one pair nearer to occipital margin than the other. Apicoscrobal setae flagellate (
Fig. 6A
). Anterior margin of scape with one or more remiform setae curved towards antennal insertion. Humeral setae filiform (
Fig. 6B
). Pair of erect setae located in the antero-medial area of pronotum filiform (
Fig. 6B
). Setae on petiole, postpetiole and fourth abdominal tergite remiform to slightly clavate.

HEAD. Masticatory margin of mandible with six preapical denticles (
Fig. 6A
). Apex of mandible with two minute intercalary denticles (
Fig. 6A
). Anterior clypeal margin, in dorsal view, convex medially. Eye, in lateral view, with three ommatidia in the longest row. Eye located in the anterior half of head. In dorsal view, scape cylindrical. Third flagellomere smaller than fourth flagellomere; length of former almost a third of length of latter.

METASOMA. Petiolar node, in dorsal view, wider than long; in lateral view, anterior margin longer than dorsal margin. Anterior margin of postpetiole, in dorsal view, medially concave. Lateral and ventral spongiform processes of petiole absent. Ventral spongiform lobe of postpetiole small (
Fig. 6B
). Lateral spongiform lobe of postpetiole minute, almost vestigial (
Fig. 6B
). Ventral basigastral spongiform pad reduced to curved (U-shaped in anterior view) carina.
